result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Jose R Godina Jr was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jose R Godina in court with attorney Dennis P Coffey.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a no contest plea to count #1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1. Count #2 is dismissed by operation of law. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Coffey makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant makes Statements. The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT#1:

IMPOSED SENTENCE OF 

3 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 11 days)
  -  18 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  18 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Victim Impact Panel to be completed. Defendant to serve 30 days huber, consecutive, as penalty for failure to attend Victim Impact Panel.
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done (no surcharges).

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $30.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - to be forwarded to City of Waukesha Police Department);

FINE:  $3039.00 + 250.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);
SEARCH WARRANT FEE: $8.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - to be forwarded to Waukesha County District Attorney's Office)
